The paper presents a new methodology for reducing the number of parameters in RNNs while maintaining performance, which is relevant to several areas of computer science. The focus on natural language processing and speech data analysis suggests that the paper may belong to cs.CL. The use of RNNs and their variations, which are commonly used in machine learning, suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.NE. Finally, the mention of experiments on natural language modeling suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.CV, which includes computer vision and image processing.
